BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunaiskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 1 June TASS -- A Russian naval delegation, 
led by commander-in-chief of the Russian naval forces Admiral 
Feliks Gromov, arrived for a three-day visit in Sevastopol in 
the morning today, the chief base of the Black Sea Navy, 
ITAR-TASS has learned from naval headquarters. 
  The delegation includes 20 top officers, including chiefs of 
departments and services of the chief naval staff and the 
Russian Defence Ministry. The purpose of the visit is to 
discuss the future of the fleet with the Black Sea Navy Command, 
to draw up proposals for the inter-governmental agreement on the 
Black Sea Navy, and to study the situation in places where the 
navy is based. 
  Admiral Gromov is expected to meet commander-in-chief of the 
Black Sea Navy Admiral Eduard Baltin today. 
  ITAR-TASS has learned that it is planned to set up a Russian 
team of experts to work on the elaboration of documents on the 
Black Sea Navy together with a similar Ukrainian team. 

